  "extract": "Ubuntu is a Linux distribution based on Debian and composed primarily of free and open-source software. Developed by the British company Canonical and a community of contributors under a meritocratic governance model, Ubuntu is released in multiple official editions: Desktop, Server, and Core for IoT and robotic devices.",
  "extract_html": "<p><b>Ubuntu</b> is a Linux distribution based on Debian and composed primarily of free and open-source software. Developed by the British company Canonical and a community of contributors under a meritocratic governance model, Ubuntu is released in multiple official editions: <i>Desktop</i>, <i>Server</i>, and <i>Core</i> for IoT and robotic devices.</p>"
